rComments: Dr. Baxter is a very caring, informational, and engaging prof. He explains tough concepts very eloquently and provides plenty of examples to help students connect ideas and understand the material better. I struggled with completing the first midterm in a timely manner and he reached out to me to support me and made the next midterm shorter!

Literally one of my fave profs. He is accessible outside of class, never leaves a question unanswered, and is very considerate of students' circumstances. I literally am his biggest fan and would get his name tattooed on my forehead. The content is difficult, but the prof makes stats fun somehow (i literally failed HS math btw). 10000000% recommend

Big fan of Dr. Baxter. He has an amazing sense of humour and makes lectures very enjoyable to watch. Assignments are fair, and he is always available outside of class for help if it's needed. He respects his students and treats us as equals. 
I would definitely take another course with him. 
Highly recommend.

Daniel Baxter was easily one of my favourite profs! You can tell he's very passionate about what he does and very knowledgable. Great, engaging and hilarious lectures. He makes relatable examples which is always great. His exams were all take home, with one research assignment. All in all super nice and chill guy, cares a lot about his students.

One of the best professors I have met, he is super caring towards his students and will go out of his way to make content interesting. I had to use the textbook to understand/learn some concepts, but the lectures contain the bulk of the information you'll need to know. Attend the live lectures. I would take one of his classes again 100%!!
Amazing prof! He makes the class interesting and it is clear he cares about his students. Also has a great sense of humour and tells the best stories.

Professor Baxter is probably the most personable teacher ive had so far. He really values the students opinions regarding his teaching styles / evaluations so he can make the class experience great. He wants his students to thrive and his actions really reflect that. I will be searching for his name in future course selection!!

Dr. Baxter is super funny but I find his lectures to be a tad too long with lots of irrelevant tangents. Perhaps the 7-10pm class or the online format is what gave me this impression. First midterm was awfully hard and vague but he adjusted the format for the second midterm and final. Would recommend taking it with him.

Great prof and great guy in general. Super chill. Caring. Very accommodating and responsive. Slides are amazing. Two open-book midterms + assignment to relate constructs to person experience, which is great. Very open, honest, and respectful. Encourages discussions.

First time I've had him as a prof and loved his course! I took Social Psych (PSY2110) and found his lectures easy to follow as he posts the powerpoints beforehand and elaborates on them in a way that added to the learning experience. Topics were interesting and his letures are fun. He's also just really funny and seems very caring and passionate!

Daniel is an amazing prof! so easy going and funny too! It is so easy to be engaged in the class content. He is very fair when it comes to assignments and tests. I would highly recommend taking his classes.
Super funny, chill prof. Because it was online there were no MC exams, just papers and take-homes. If you pay attention and take your time, you can get an easy A+ in the course.

Super chill professor but just not for me. He said the textbook was optional in the beginning of the course, but I genuinely feel that it is needed for this course and the midterms are useless without the textbook. He also kept referring to the text but ? I thought it was optional. Still a good prof and keeps his classes fun.

I learned a lot from this class. I had hoped for multiple choice exams, but because of online learning it was take home written assignments. It was a lot of reading, but he took in students feedback. Professor Baxter is very approachable and friendly. Lectures were engaging with lots of laughter!

The course was based on 3 assignments. Still awaiting my mark for second assignment (which was supposed to come out a month ago). I did well for the final because I cited every single point so remember to cite. I would say the course is not very organized because it was run for the first time. Lectures were okay but studied mostly by textbook.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: 3 assignments including the final. Im still waiting for 2 of these grades. Hes a very funny guy and seems really nice. For a first time prof, he was great. Assignments are super fair. Although the turnaround time for grades is horrible. Overall, i recommend him!
Although I feel like this class would have been better off with MC exams, I do think that he is an amazing professor. He is so funny and polite. Love his vibe.
Really funny prof! Assignments are fair. Really liked him.

Overall, a very funny and nice professor. Makes a 8:30 am class so entertaining. Initially, there were 3 papers but after the first one, he realized it was too long and time consuming so he changed the papers to take-home exams which were like short answer questions. Exams are fair if you know the material! Totally worth taking him.
